resources.string: If my drive is less than 400 miles one way, will i still get reimbursed for mileage?
Can I fly to my work location, then drive back and still get reimbursed for both the flight and the mileage?
Can I take the AutoTrain and get reimbursed for the AutoTrain and claim the mileage of the trip as well?
Can I buy a 1 way flight ticket to my work location and then buy another 1 way ticket for the way back since I dont know my end date yet?
Can I get $35 a day for meals even If i spend only $20?
Yes, you need to note the miles on the T&L form and include the MapQuest map
You need to get permission from Kim Demko first. Then get a reciept for the fuel.
All end dates are on the co-op intern website.
No it is not per diem. It is the max allowance.
can I provide a credit card billing statement instead of receipts?
No, must be a copy of the itemized receipt showing date and city.
Can I get reimbursed in advance for my baggage fees, hotels or tolls for my return trip?
No, we must have paid receipts for those items.
If my friend or family member drives with me to my work location, can I get reimbursed for their meals/hotel costs?
No, GE only reimburses items that the employee incurs.
Can I submit a T&L form for reimbursement even if it more than 2 weeks after my end date?
No, due to accounting practices we are not able to process 2 weeks past your end date.
If for any reason I have to leave my rotation earlier than the expected end date, do I still get to keep the full reimbursement?
No, it will be prorated for the actual weeks that you were working. Payroll would send you an overpayment letter for the recoupment of funds.
If I am unsure whether an item can be reimbursed what shouldI do?
PRIOR to making an travel arrangements or actually travelling you must email Aviation.CoopTLforms@ge.com to get approval.
